      <T n="text">0xA581BA9D<!--<font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font> can be caught by Sims in a variety of ways and will cause unpredictable effects. These aren't all bad though! Sims may periodically cough up Simoleons or may find they're able to repair things much faster, even if their sneezes occasionally break things around them. Sims with an Ailment will also have visible symptoms on their skin and will occasionally cough, itch, sniff themselves, or have angry outbursts.\n\nAilments can be contracted from contagious sources like using a toilet away from the home lot, going to work, or interacting with other Sims who have an Ailment! Sims who become <font color="#199C2C"><b>Very Imbalanced</b></font> will come down with an Ailment if they don't already have one.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Ailments_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:831218fc0ffa27ee</T>
      <T n="text">0x3CC625EB<!--Regardless of how a Sim gets an Ailment, there are a few ways to cure it:\n\n• Sims can choose to wait it out! Ailments will pass after a few days with no lingering effects.\n• Create a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Cure</b></font> at an <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Table</b></font> using the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Skill</b></font>.\n• <font color="#199C2C"><b>Visit a Naturopath</b></font> via the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Phone</b></font> under Home.\n• Ask a Friendly Fairy to cure it.\n• <font color="#199C2C"><b>Manifest Ailment Relief</b></font> at Moondrop Springs in the Everdew neighborhood.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
